<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
This species is easily diagnosed among all 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Sporades" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sporades" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Sporades</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the male aedeagus, wherein the median lobe is expanded and twisted apically (
<bibRefCitation author="Jeannel, R" journalOrPublisher="L'Abeille" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="221 - 550" refId="B17" refString="Jeannel, R, 1926. Monographie des Trechinae, Morphologie comparee et distribution geographique d'un groupe de Coleopteres (1). L'Abeille 32: 221 - 550" title="Monographie des Trechinae, Morphologie comparee et distribution geographique d'un groupe de Coleopteres (1)." volume="32" year="1926">Jeannel 1926</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 288; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ueno, S-I" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the National Science Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="27 - 36" refId="B24" refString="Ueno, S-I, 1966. The New Caledonian trechodines of the genus Sporades (Coleoptera, Trechinae). Bulletin of the National Science Museum 9: 27 - 36" title="The New Caledonian trechodines of the genus Sporades (Coleoptera, Trechinae)." volume="9" year="1966">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Uéno">Ueno</normalizedToken>
1966
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 5). A single male of this species was examined (MHNW) to establish the distributional record reported below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<bibRefCitation author="Giachino, PM" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="47 - 54" refId="B15" refString="Giachino, PM, 2012. On the genus Sporades Fauvel, 1882 (Coleoptera: Carabidae, Trechini) with the description of three new species from New Caledonia. Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona 36: 47 - 54" title="On the genus Sporades Fauvel, 1882 (Coleoptera: Carabidae, Trechini) with the description of three new species from New Caledonia." volume="36" year="2012">Giachino (2012)</bibRefCitation>
summarized the distributional records of 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. sexpunctatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="sexpunctatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">S. sexpunctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on examined material, showing that this species maintains a broad geographical distribution across the southern half of Grande Terre (
<bibRefCitation author="Giachino, PM" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="47 - 54" refId="B15" refString="Giachino, PM, 2012. On the genus Sporades Fauvel, 1882 (Coleoptera: Carabidae, Trechini) with the description of three new species from New Caledonia. Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona 36: 47 - 54" title="On the genus Sporades Fauvel, 1882 (Coleoptera: Carabidae, Trechini) with the description of three new species from New Caledonia." volume="36" year="2012">Giachino 2012</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 11). Summarizing all published distributional records for this species, easily diagnosed by the male aedeagus (
<bibRefCitation author="Fauvel, A" journalOrPublisher="Revue d'Entomologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="217 - 236" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/title/10428page/231/mode/1up" refId="B13" refString="Fauvel, A, 1882. Les Coleopteres de la Nouvelle-Caledonie et dependances avec descriptions, notes et synonymies nouvelles. Revue d'Entomologie 1: 217 - 236, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/title/10428page/231/mode/1up" title="Les Coleopteres de la Nouvelle-Caledonie et dependances avec descriptions, notes et synonymies nouvelles." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/title/10428page/231/mode/1up" volume="1" year="1882">Fauvel 1882</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Fauvel, A" journalOrPublisher="Revue d'Entomologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="203 - 378" publicationUrl="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/10976669" refId="B14" refString="Fauvel, A, 1903. Faune analytique des Coleopteres de la Nouvelle-Caledonie. Revue d'Entomologie 22: 203 - 378, https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/10976669" title="Faune analytique des Coleopteres de la Nouvelle-Caledonie." url="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/10976669" volume="22" year="1903">1903</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Jeannel, R" journalOrPublisher="L'Abeille" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="221 - 550" refId="B17" refString="Jeannel, R, 1926. Monographie des Trechinae, Morphologie comparee et distribution geographique d'un groupe de Coleopteres (1). L'Abeille 32: 221 - 550" title="Monographie des Trechinae, Morphologie comparee et distribution geographique d'un groupe de Coleopteres (1)." volume="32" year="1926">Jeannel 1926</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ueno, S-I" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the National Science Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="27 - 36" refId="B24" refString="Ueno, S-I, 1966. The New Caledonian trechodines of the genus Sporades (Coleoptera, Trechinae). Bulletin of the National Science Museum 9: 27 - 36" title="The New Caledonian trechodines of the genus Sporades (Coleoptera, Trechinae)." volume="9" year="1966">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Uéno">Ueno</normalizedToken>
1966
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Donabauer, M" journalOrPublisher="Entomofauna" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="385 - 391" refId="B12" refString="Donabauer, M, 2011. Two new Sporades (Coleoptera: Carabidae: Trechinae) from New Caledonia. Entomofauna 32: 385 - 391" title="Two new Sporades (Coleoptera: Carabidae: Trechinae) from New Caledonia." volume="32" year="2011">Donabauer 2011</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Giachino, PM" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="47 - 54" refId="B15" refString="Giachino, PM, 2012. On the genus Sporades Fauvel, 1882 (Coleoptera: Carabidae, Trechini) with the description of three new species from New Caledonia. Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona 36: 47 - 54" title="On the genus Sporades Fauvel, 1882 (Coleoptera: Carabidae, Trechini) with the description of three new species from New Caledonia." volume="36" year="2012">Giachino 2012</bibRefCitation>
), results in a distributional estimate based on 29 specimens (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 6. Distributional records for Sporades sexpunctatus; asterisked locality first reported herein." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.908.48707.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/376193" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">6</figureCitation>
). To these can be added one male: New Caledonia, N-Prov., Tendo 10 km WSW 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hienghène">Hienghene</normalizedToken>
, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="20" direction="south" minutes="42" orientation="latitude" precision="15" seconds="46" value="-20.712778">20°42'46&quot;S</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate degrees="164" direction="east" minutes="48" orientation="longitude" precision="15" seconds="56" value="164.81555">164°48'56&quot;E</geoCoordinate>
, 2.IX.1970, leg. H. Franz (M. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Jäch">Jaech</normalizedToken>
pers. comm.). This most-recently documented locality extends the known distribution of 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. sexpunctatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="sexpunctatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">S. sexpunctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
well northward in the Northern Province of Grande Terre. The known localities range in elevation 20-390 m, with the species repeatedly collected at sites above 300 m elevation: e.g., Col d'Amieu, Table Unio on the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Serraméa-Canala">Serramea-Canala</normalizedToken>
Road, Parc des Grandes 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Fougères">Fougeres</normalizedToken>
, near Thio, and on Mt. Koghi (
<bibRefCitation author="Giachino, PM" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="47 - 54" refId="B15" refString="Giachino, PM, 2012. On the genus Sporades Fauvel, 1882 (Coleoptera: Carabidae, Trechini) with the description of three new species from New Caledonia. Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona 36: 47 - 54" title="On the genus Sporades Fauvel, 1882 (Coleoptera: Carabidae, Trechini) with the description of three new species from New Caledonia." volume="36" year="2012">Giachino 2012</bibRefCitation>
). Beetles have been collected at the margins of small streams, along a small stream in a ravine, and by splashing gravel bars along streams at night or during the day.
</paragraph>
